btrplace.model

Interface Attributes

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAttributes

    public interface Attributes
extends Cloneable
    Allow to specify attributes related to managed elements. Attributes are key/value pairs, where values are Java primitives (integer, double, String, boolean)
    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier

      • castAndPut

        boolean castAndPut(Element e,
                   String k,
                   String v)
        Put a value but try to cast into to a supported primitive if possible. First, it tries to cast v first to a boolean, then to a integer value, finally to a double value. If none of the cast succeeded, the value is let as a string.
        Parameters:
        e - the element
        k - the attribute identifier
        v - the value to set
        Returns:
        true if a previous value was overridden
